## Purpose

FinSphere helps South African users take full control of their personal finances through
structured budgeting, intelligent goal tracking, visual analytics, and behavioural gamification.
All data is stored locally using Room DB (SQLite) for full offline capability.

---

## Features

### Core Features (Part 2)
- User registration and secure login with SHA-256 password hashing
- Create budget categories with custom colour coding
- Add expense entries with date, start time, end time, amount, and description
- Take and store a photo per expense entry using the device camera
- View expense list filtered by a user-selectable period
- Access stored photo from the expense list detail view
- View total spending per category for a user-selectable period
- Set minimum and maximum spending goals per category

### New Features (Part 3)
- Spending graph: bar chart showing amount spent per category with min/max goal limit lines
- Goal progress: visual display of spending progress relative to goals for the current month
- Gamification: 6 unlockable achievement badges with a points system

---

## Own Feature 1: Smart Expense Search

Search all expense entries in real time by typing a keyword from the description.
Results filter instantly as the user types, allowing quick retrieval of any transaction
without needing to scroll through the full list or set a date range.
Accessible from the dashboard under Own Features.

Justification: Users who log many expenses need a fast way to locate specific transactions.
This feature significantly improves usability and daily engagement with the application.

---

## Own Feature 2: Financial Health Score

A composite score from 0 to 100 measuring overall financial discipline across three components:
- Budget adherence (40 points): percentage of categories within their maximum spending goal
- Logging activity (30 points): number of expense entries logged in the current month
- Goal coverage (30 points): percentage of categories that have goals assigned

The score provides a grade (Excellent, Good, Fair, Needs Work) with personalised advice.
Accessible from the dashboard under Own Features.

Justification: A single easy-to-understand metric summarises overall financial health,
encouraging consistent logging and goal-setting behaviour through a gamified score.

